rComments: She's a Canadian hero. My condolences  to those who do not feel she is engaging enough on the details of the CBCA. Try to do better, if you can. It's dry. But she's not.  Easy to look at, etc. Plus, a walking tank of info. If you ask her about a related topic of interest, she will give you a number of sources to set your course.(figuratively).
Not completely satisfied with this class.

Knows the UN system very well. A bit abrasive. A bit confrontational and quirky. Does not provide feedback to students at all or in timely fashion. Tough grader. Has interesting pedagogy and doesn't simply lecture. More interested in her research than teaching but overall an effective instructor. Recommended!

Course: Transnational Corporations and Human Rights. She is one of the best Profs I've ever had. She is passionate about the subject matter, yet conveys it objectively and from different angles. She is very respectful towards students and takes a real interest in their interests and careers. I would definitely take the course with her again!
Prof Simons is a great prof, really knowledgeable and approachable. Gives good feedback but doesn't spoon feed.
